summary:
Highly-motivated, creative and collaborative leader who uses workshop delivery, process improvement, and project management strengths to attain business goals and drive efficiency. Expert in gathering, documenting, and prioritizing requirements into clear, understandable and actionable user stories, use cases and acceptance test criteria. Skilled at communicating and collaborating across organization with all levels including senior executives, business leaders, technical and cross-functional teams.

Expertise in:

Business Analysis, Research & Design
• Designed proof-of-concept for travel distribution platform by conducting gap analysis, eliciting business requirements, and designing wireframes
• Facilitated workshops to develop, analyze and deliver process flows, business requirements, use cases and test cases
• Identified opportunities for process improvements through component business modeling, as-is pain point analysis and requirements elicitation

Strategic Problem-Solving & Strategy Development
• Developed strategic roadmap prioritizing system enhancements providing a holistic view of the customer, optimized utilization of inventory, maximized marketing opportunities, enhanced guest experience, and customer self-service capabilities
• Led ideation workshops to identify enhancement opportunities to solution portfolio resulting in more customized industry specific offerings
• Created go-to-market plans for industry solutions and business partner joint ventures

Leadership, Development & Communication
• Gained alignment across program leadership and communicated key updates through the implementation of a communications strategy
• Applied agile approach to manage project scope, schedule, financials, and staffing
• Led 6-person team, winning runner-up in competition to create strategy and marketing material

projects.title: Team Lead - System enhancements and integration for leading airline
projects.description:
Led the Integration Management Team of 10 consultants. Advised program leadership and executive management on program readiness including technology and business readiness, change management, program communications, and program management. Accountable for integration strategy development, process transformation, and technical event planning.

Key Accomplishments:
• Designed issue management processes and strategy to support critical operations during integration and data migration for systems impacting over 25,000 employees. Facilitated the training program, and managed the 24/7, day-to-day Issue Management Team (over 100 people) operations during product enhancement deployments and integration cutovers.
• Managed the Integration Management Team (10 consultants). Improved responsibly, accountability, efficiency and team morale by defining roles, balancing workload, streamlining processes and redistributing work based on interests and experience.
• Developed an integration strategy and roadmap to drive towards a single set of policies, systems and processes based on best practices and experience from previous integrations.
• Created an integrated master schedule to coordinate an employee system integration cutover (impacting 25,000 employees) followed by a data migration cutover. Work involved identifying and coordinating the timelines for both policy and tool development across a broad range of employee classifications.
